        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1068876064" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13784881933466883929">Probably the favorite play read until now, which I have to admit are not many. A linguist makes a bet that he can turn a flower girl into a lady in 6 months. Both the girls and the linguist are strong characters and from there conflicts arise. By the end of the play they get attached to each other in a strange way. What I found special about the play was the afterword written by the author himself that explains in details how the life of the character will unfold. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


