<div id="review_2388494465" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2388494465" />
    <a title="Arybo ✨" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50870096-arybo"><img alt="Arybo ✨" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618160577p2/50870096.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2388494465?book_show_action=true">May 23, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Arybo ✨" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Arybo ✨" href="/user/show/50870096-arybo">Arybo ✨</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140450224" href="/book/show/877250.Pygmalion">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=theatre">theatre</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=read-in-english-or-spanish">read-in-english-or-spanish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=travellingaroundtheworld">travellingaroundtheworld</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=english-classics">english-classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=read-in-2018">read-in-2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=author-s">author-s</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=rory-gilmore-reading-list">rory-gilmore-reading-list</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50870096-arybo?shelf=from-the-library">from-the-library</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2388494465" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2018032616186125104">🇬🇧 <i> My Fair Lady </i> was the first film I saw with Audrey Hepburn, after attending the musical that was going around in Italy some time ago. I was a bit disturbed by the vision at the theater, not because I did not like the plot, but because of the attitude of the actors and the choice of the translation into Italian. Back home, I decided to watch the movie. And I fell in love with it. Literally. Now I know almost all the songs (in Italian, shame on me), and I still sing them as I clean my house.<br/>It</span>
  <span id="freeText2018032616186125104" style="display:none">🇬🇧 <i> My Fair Lady </i> was the first film I saw with Audrey Hepburn, after attending the musical that was going around in Italy some time ago. I was a bit disturbed by the vision at the theater, not because I did not like the plot, but because of the attitude of the actors and the choice of the translation into Italian. Back home, I decided to watch the movie. And I fell in love with it. Literally. Now I know almost all the songs (in Italian, shame on me), and I still sing them as I clean my house.<br />It was a long time that I wanted to read the true story of Shaw. I was not disappointed, although I expected a play a bit longer. I am happy to have read the end added by the author in 1941 (if I'm not mistaken). This finale is more understandable than that rewritten by television producers and others.<br /><br />In addition, I would like to say that the section on Pygmalion and Galatea in Ovid's <i>Metamorphosis</i> is one of the most beautiful pieces in the Latin literature. 💘<br /><br />——————-<br /><br />🇮🇹<i>My Fair Lady</i> è stato il mio primo film con Audrey Hepburn, dopo aver assistito al musical che girava in Italia un po’ di tempo fa. Ero rimasta un po’ turbata dalla visione a teatro, non perché non mi fosse piaciuta la trama, quanto per l’atteggiamento degli attori e la scelta della traduzione in italiano. Tornata a casa, ho deciso di guardare il film. E me ne sono innamorata. Letteralmente. Ora conosco quasi tutte le canzoni (in italiano, shame on me), ed ancora le canto quanto pulisco casa.<br />Era da tanto, quindi, che volevo leggere la storia vera di Shaw. Non sono rimasta delusa, sebbene mi aspettassi un play un po’ più corposo. Sono felice di aver letto la fine aggiunta dall’autore nel 1941 (se non sbaglio). È più comprensibile questo finale rispetto a quello riscritto da produttori televisivi e simili. <br />In aggiunta, vorrei dire che la sezione riguardante Pigmalione e Galatea nelle <i>Metamorfosi</i> di Ovidio è una dei pezzi più belli nella letteratura latina.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2018032616186125104" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


